{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "We used the best-performing model provided by Reimers and Gurevych [60] (all-mpnet-base-v2; see [61]), showing good model performance when fine-tuned on a set of natural language processing (NLP) tasks.",
    "Model performance was evaluated on the basis of the Sentence Embedding Benchmark, which uses a set of clustering, binary classification, retrieval, reranking, and semantic textual similarity tasks (see [60]).",
    "This model allowed us to map sentences to vectors capturing their semantic information.",
    "These vectors can then be used to compute measures of similarity.",
    "We used cosine similarity ( S c (a, b) ∈ [-1, 1]; see, e.g., [70]) to quantify semantic similarity between tweets ( a) and the respective claim ( b)."
  ],
